<p>I want to submit a form. It is just an Authentication page, with fields like username, password and grant type.</p>  <p>I am trying to do it in both the ways  1. Using plain Javascript(XmlHttpRequest) 2. Using jQuery</p>  <p>There are 2 request headers I need to set: 1. Authorization 2. Content-Type</p>  <p>But when using plain javascript I am not sure how to pass above mention parameters in the request body and also how to set request headers.</p>  <p>While using jQuery I am not getting how to post form data.</p>  <p>I am posting my code below.</p>  <p><strong>This is using jQuery Ajax</strong></p>  <pre><code>&lt;html&gt; &lt;head&gt; &lt;script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.11.3/jquery.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt; &lt;script&gt; $("#ajaxform").submit(function(e) {     var postData = $(this).serializeArray();     var formURL = $(this).attr("action");     $.ajax(     {         url : formURL,         type: "POST",         beforeSend: function (request)         {             request.setRequestHeader("Authorization", "*****");             request.setRequestHeader("contentType", "application/json;charset=UTF-8");         },         data : postData,         success:function(data, textStatus, jqXHR)          {             alert(data);         },         error: function(jqXHR, textStatus, errorThrown)          {         }     });     e.preventDefault(); //STOP default action });  $("#ajaxform").submit(); //SUBMIT FORM &lt;/script&gt; &lt;/head&gt; &lt;body&gt;  &lt;form name="ajaxform" id="ajaxform" action="someurl" method="POST"&gt;     Username: &lt;input type="text" name="username" value ="someusername"/&gt; &lt;br/&gt;     Password: &lt;input type="password" name="password" value ="somepassword" /&gt; &lt;br/&gt;     Grant Type: &lt;input type="text" name="grant_type" value="somevalue"/&gt; &lt;br/&gt;     &lt;input type="submit" value="Submit"&gt; &lt;/form&gt;  &lt;/body&gt; &lt;/html&gt; </code></pre>  <p><strong>This is using plain javascript:</strong></p>  <pre><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt; &lt;html&gt; &lt;head&gt; &lt;script&gt; function userLogin(callback) {     var xmlhttp;     var url = "someurl"      var uname = document.getElementById("username").value;     var pwd = document.getElementById("password").value;     var grantType = document.getElementById("grant_type").value;      var data = 'username' + window.encodeURIComponent(uname)     + 'password' + window.encodeURIComponent(pwd) + 'grant_type' + window.encodeURIComponent(grantType) ;      if (window.XMLHttpRequest)     {// code for IE7+, Firefox, Chrome, Opera, Safari         xmlhttp=new XMLHttpRequest();     }     else     {// code for IE6, IE5         xmlhttp=new ActiveXObject("Microsoft.XMLHTTP");     }     xmlhttp.onreadystatechange=function()     {         if (xmlhttp.readyState==4 &amp;&amp; xmlhttp.status == 200)         {              //var some=xmlhttp.responseXML.documentElement;             var response = xmlhttp.responseText;             //console.log(response)             callback(xmlhttp.responseText);         }     }     xmlhttp.open("POST", url, true);     xmlhttp.setRequestHeader('Authorization', '******');     xmlhttp.setRequestHeader('Content-Type', 'application/json;charset=UTF-8');     xmlhttp.send(data); } function userLoginCallback(response){     if(response != null){         var div = document.getElementById("result");         div.innerHTML = response;     } } &lt;/script&gt; &lt;/head&gt; &lt;body&gt; &lt;form action=""&gt;   Username:&lt;br&gt;   &lt;input id="username" type="text" name="username" value="someusername"&gt;   &lt;br&gt;   Password:&lt;br&gt;   &lt;input id="password" type="password" name="password" value="somepassword"&gt;   &lt;br&gt;    Grant Type:&lt;br&gt;   &lt;input id="grant_type" type="text" name="grant_type" value="somevalue"&gt;    &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;   &lt;input type="submit" value="Submit" onclick="userLogin(userLoginCallback)"&gt; &lt;/form&gt;  &lt;div id="result"&gt;  &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/body&gt; &lt;/html&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Please correct me where I am doing wrong. Thanks</p>